verbose_text: A large case-control study also found that in females, frequent use of oral contraceptives without progesterone, older age at first delivery, a lack of lactation history, and nulliparity were significantly associated with an increased risk of GC [XREF_BIBR], which may support the harmful role of estrogen in GCYA in females.
